<p class=3D"ltx_p" id=3D"S3.I3.i2.p1.8">Here <math alttext=3D"\theta:\Omega=
\times\mathcal{T}\to\Omega" class=3D"ltx_Math" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.=
I3.i2.p1.3.m1" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><mrow><mi>=CE=B8</mi><mo lspa=
ce=3D"0.278em" rspace=3D"0.278em">:</mo><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=3D"norm=
al">=CE=A9</mi><mo lspace=3D"0.222em" rspace=3D"0.222em">=C3=97</mo><mi cla=
ss=3D"ltx_font_mathcaligraphic">=F0=9D=92=AF</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=3D"fal=
se">=E2=86=92</mo><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=A9</mi></mrow></mrow><anno=
tation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\theta:\Omega\times\mathcal{T}\to\Ome=
ga</annotation></semantics></math>
is a map that is part of the definition of the random dynamical system,
and specifies a deterministic rule for updating the sample point <math altt=
ext=3D"\omega^{\prime}" class=3D"ltx_Math" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.I3.i=
2.p1.4.m2" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><msup><mi>=CF=89</mi><mo>=E2=80=
=B2</mo></msup><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\omega^{\prime}</=
annotation></semantics></math>
and the dynamical map <math alttext=3D"f_{\omega^{\prime}}" class=3D"ltx_Ma=
th" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.I3.i2.p1.5.m3" intent=3D":literal"><semanti=
cs><msub><mi>f</mi><msup><mi>=CF=89</mi><mo>=E2=80=B2</mo></msup></msub><an=
notation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">f_{\omega^{\prime}}</annotation></s=
emantics></math> to accommodate replacing
the original initial time <math alttext=3D"0" class=3D"ltx_Math" display=3D=
"inline" id=3D"S3.I3.i2.p1.6.m4" intent=3D":literal"><mn>0</mn></math> with=
 the effectively new initial time
<math alttext=3D"t^{\prime}" class=3D"ltx_Math" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3=
.I3.i2.p1.7.m5" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><msup><mi>t</mi><mo>=E2=80=
=B2</mo></msup><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">t^{\prime}</annot=
ation></semantics></math>. That is, <math alttext=3D"\theta" class=3D"ltx_M=
ath" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.I3.i2.p1.8.m6" intent=3D":literal"><semant=
ics><mi>=CE=B8</mi><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\theta</annot=
ation></semantics></math> is necessary to account for any
deterministic evolution in the underlying source of randomness itself.</p><=
button class=3D"sr-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Report issue for p=
receding element</button>
</div>
</li>
