<section class=3D"ltx_section" id=3D"S4">
<h2 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_title_section">
<span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_section">4 </span>The Stochastic-Quantum The=
orem</h2><button class=3D"sr-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Report i=
ssue for preceding element</button>
<section class=3D"ltx_subsection" id=3D"S4.SS1">
<h3 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_title_subsection">
<span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsection">4.1 </span>Statement of the Theo=
rem</h3><button class=3D"sr-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Report is=
sue for preceding element</button>
<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S4.SS1.p1">
<p class=3D"ltx_p" id=3D"S4.SS1.p1.1">Focusing on the case of indivisible s=
tochastic processes with finite
configuration spaces (leaving the more general case to future work),
this paper=E2=80=99s next major goal will be to present a self-contained pr=
oof
of the following theorem, which is a new result that implicitly also
appeared in other work (Barandes 2025).</p><button class=3D"sr-only button"=
 style=3D"display: none;">Report issue for preceding element</button>
</div>
<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S4.SS1.p2">
<table class=3D"ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table" id=3D"S4.E69">
<tbody><tr class=3D"ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class=3D"ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class=3D"ltx_eqn_cell ltx_align_center"><math alttext=3D"\boxed{\begin{=
subarray}{c}{\displaystyle\textbf{The Stochastic-Quantum Theorem}}\\
\ \\
{\displaystyle\textrm{Every indivisible stochastic process}}\\
{\displaystyle\textrm{can be regarded as a subsystem of a}}\\
{\displaystyle\textrm{unistochastic process.}}\end{subarray}}" class=3D"ltx=
_Math" display=3D"block" id=3D"S4.E69.m1" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><m=
enclose notation=3D"box"><mtable displaystyle=3D"true" rowspacing=3D"0pt"><=
mtr><mtd><mtext class=3D"ltx_mathvariant_bold" mathsize=3D"0.700em">The Sto=
chastic-Quantum Theorem</mtext></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd>=
<mtext mathsize=3D"0.700em">Every indivisible stochastic process</mtext></m=
td></mtr><mtr><mtd><mtext mathsize=3D"0.700em">can be regarded as a subsyst=
em of a</mtext></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mtext mathsize=3D"0.700em">unistochas=
tic process.</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></menclose><annotation encoding=3D=
"application/x-tex">\boxed{\begin{subarray}{c}{\displaystyle\textbf{The Sto=
chastic-Quantum Theorem}}\\
\ \\
{\displaystyle\textrm{Every indivisible stochastic process}}\\
{\displaystyle\textrm{can be regarded as a subsystem of a}}\\
{\displaystyle\textrm{unistochastic process.}}\end{subarray}}</annotation><=
/semantics></math></td>
<td class=3D"ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padright"></td>
<td class=3D"ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_eqno ltx_align_middle ltx_align_right" ro=
